{"word":"θρεπτέος","slug":"θρεπτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θρεπτέος</b></el> <el>(θρεπτέος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:τρέφω'><el>τρέφω</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be fed</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>θρεπτέον</el>, <i>one must feed</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>from <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <i>one must be fed, one must live</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}